notes.name: Mount Treton
notes.legend: Dormant volcano. Height: 3364 m.

notes.name: Hot Springs of Buckingham
notes.legend: A geothermal springs with naturally heated water that provide relaxation and medicinal benefits. Average temperature is 38¬∞C.

notes.name: Dyonsshar Purifying Well
notes.legend: This legendary water source is whispered about in ancient tales and believed to possess mystical properties. The spring emanates crystal-clear water, shimmering with an otherworldly iridescence that sparkles even in the dimmest light.

notes.name: Mungeong ‚Äî copper mining town
notes.legend: Mungeong is a mining town of 1362 people just nearby the copper mine.

notes.name: Melloraquen ‚Äî salt mining town
notes.legend: Melloraquen is a mining town of 814 people just nearby the salt mine.

notes.name: Towbover Bridge
notes.legend: An old crossing of the Towbover River, rarely used since banditry infested the area.

notes.name: The Hungry Owl
notes.legend: A big and famous roadside inn. Delicious stuffed badger with black wine is served here.

notes.name: Helsborough Lighthouse
notes.legend: A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea.

notes.name: Burporley Waterfall
notes.legend: A breathtaking waterfall cuts through the landscape.

notes.name: Ungcheonese Waterfall
notes.legend: A gorgeous waterfall flows here.

notes.name: Thatcking Waterfall
notes.legend: A breathtaking waterfall cuts through the landscape.

notes.name: Pestelforga Battlefield
notes.legend:
A historical battle of the Cerganan Conflict. 
Date: December 29, 390 Khazinb Era.

notes.name: Dungeon
notes.legend: Undiscovered dungeon. See One page dungeon

notes.name: Tresey Monster
notes.legend: Old sailors tell stories of a gigantic sea monster inhabiting these dangerous waters. Rumors say it can be 38 m long.

notes.name: Sobury Banshee
notes.legend: Inscriptions speak of a huge Banshee who inhabits Sobury hills and terrorizes the region.

notes.name: Bolcino Forest
notes.legend: A forest sacred to local Hetallian Spirits.

notes.name: Pirates
notes.legend: Pirate ships have been spotted in these waters.

notes.name: Ruined Town
notes.legend: Ruins of an ancient town. Untold riches may lie within.

notes.name: Azon Library
notes.legend: A vast collection of knowledge, including many rare and ancient tomes.

notes.name: Travelling Wonderous Circus
notes.legend: Roll up, roll up, this wonderous circus is here for a limited time only.

notes.name: Macham Joust
notes.legend: Warriors from around the land gather for a joust of the greats in Macham, with fame, fortune and favour on offer to the victor.

notes.name: Morbrugh Fair
notes.legend: A fair is being held in Morbrugh, with all manner of local and foreign goods and services on offer.

notes.name: Geese migration
notes.legend: A huge group of geese are migrating, whether part of their annual routine, or something more extraordinary.

notes.name: Midmanch Sinkhole
notes.legend: The Midmanch Sinkhole. Locals claim that it is the home of strange monsters.

notes.name: Abyssal Rift
notes.legend: A rumoured abyssal rift in this area is causing an emmissary to step through with an all-powerful relic.

notes.name: Disturbed Burial
notes.legend: A burial site has been disturbed in this area, causing the dead to rise and attack the living.

notes.name: Heungjin Necropolis
notes.legend: A desolate necropolis where an eerie stillness reigns. Time seems frozen amidst the decaying mausoleums, and the silence is broken only by the whispers of the wind and the rustle of tattered banners

notes.name: Random encounter
